Please align this comment message with below

I see that PCIE Temp has been moved as a separate test case so it's fine. However, I noticed that the following ones have also been removed. Is there any reason why they were taken out of the validation?

pcie_dcm0_power
io_dcm0_power
These two does not appear anymore in metric definition. Neither they look to be important as per my earlier discussion with HMC team. So, I am not including them anymore.
Okay them please add this info in the commit message.
Add comment message like in above test case about these.
Please move this dictionary to the variable section of this suite. You can also name it to somthing like - telemetry_sensor or telemetry_metric_definations
Remove white space and add example here and below
It is required - one is for loop, another for If statement.
metric_definition_name here is same as suite variable. Have a difference between these names.
Both are different - the suite variable is metric_definitions_list

Bring examples in one line like below. If you want to keep in two lines then align the example text.

    # key       Name of metric definition in plain english. Example: ambient temperature
    # value     Equivalent regex expression of telemetry definition. Example:  Ambient.*Temp
I am not doing template way here. It is just a keyword call.
${text_dict} is a suite variable.. please give a meaningful variable name.

Add To Telemetry definition Record Dictionary

please mention in which format the data is stored

key -> metric_name
value -> tele_regex_format

please provide proper variable names.. instead of key, value
I am keeping this. Variable names are here simple with all documentations added.
english_actual_teleDef --- cant this something be simplified? not appealing
Not changing again - used at several places. There is a  documentation for this variable.
done - two spaces for english_actual_teleDef, for regex_matching_output, it is fine.
